This paper is primarily focused on the performance analysis of wireless networks, specifically 60 GHz wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of moment generating functions and probabilistic analysis, which are common in the fields of information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the unique fading characteristics of the 60 GHz channel, which is a topic of interest in the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the ability of the network to satisfy quality-of-service requirements, which is a topic of interest in the field of control systems (cs.SY).
